-- M6 parity fixture: matches jl4-service/test/TestData.hs's
-- 'deonticExportJL4'. Two-tier sale contract — seller MUST deliver
-- within 14, then buyer MUST pay within 30, then FULFILLED. Either
-- side missing the deadline → BREACH.

DECLARE Party IS ONE OF `the seller`, `the buyer`
DECLARE `Contract Action` IS ONE OF `deliver the goods`, `pay the invoice`

@export default sale contract
GIVETH A DEONTIC Party `Contract Action`
`the sale contract` MEANS
    PARTY `the seller`
    MUST `deliver the goods`
    WITHIN 14
    HENCE
        PARTY `the buyer`
        MUST `pay the invoice`
        WITHIN 30
        HENCE FULFILLED
        LEST BREACH
    LEST BREACH
